quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  25,45,"Do you not see to your Lord how He extended/spread the shade ? And if He willed/wanted, He would have made it still/motionless, then We made/put the sun on it (as) a proof/evidence"
  25,46,Then We grasped it to Us easy grasping
  25,47,"And He is who made/put for you the night (as) a cover/dress, and the sleep (for) rest/sleep , and He made/put the daytime (for) revival"
  25,48,"And He is who sent the winds/breezes (as) a good news between His mercy`s hand, and We descended from the sky pure/clean water"
  25,49,"To revive with it a dead/lifeless country/land , and We give it drink from what We created (from) camels/livestock and many humans/people"
  25,50,"And We had purified it/detailed it linguistically between them (so) they mention/remember , so most of the people refused/hated except (insistent) disbelief"
  25,51,"And if We willed/wanted, We would have sent in every village/urban city a warner/giver of notice"
  25,52,So do not obey the disbelievers and struggle against them with it great struggling/defending for the faith
  25,53,"And He is who mixed/set loose the two large bodies of water that (is) fresh/delightful very sweet/fresh, and that is salty salty and bitter, and He made/put between them (B) a barrier and (an) obstruction obstructed"
  25,54,"And He is who created from the water a human so He made/put him a relationship/kinship and relations through marriage, and your Lord was/is capable/able/overpowering"
  25,55,"And they worship from other that God what does not benefit them, and nor harms them, and the disbeliever was/is on (against) his Lord a supporter/helper"
  25,56,And We did not send you except (as) an announcer of good news and a warner
  25,57,"Say: \"I do not ask/demand of you on it from a wage/fee except who willed/wanted that he takes to His Lord a way/path"
  25,58,"And rely/depend on the alive/live who does not die, and praise/glorify with His praise/gratitude , and enough/sufficient with Him, with His worshippers`/slaves` crimes (as) an expert/experienced"
  25,59,"Who created the skies/space and the earth/Planet Earth and what is between them both in six days, then He aimed/tended to on the throne , the merciful, so ask/question with Him (about) an expert/experienced"
  25,60,"And if (it) was said to them: \"Prostrate to the merciful.\" They said: \"And what (is) the merciful? Do we prostrate to what you order/command us?\" And (it) increased them hastening away with aversion"